# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Unified file-handling policy for the Higgins system  (RWA · HUF · Hˢ)
# This file is IDENTICAL in all three repositories — keep it that way.
#
# Policy: store every file as an ordinary Git object. No Git LFS.
#   • Text is normalized to LF so the three repos stay byte-identical
#     across machines and operating systems (no CRLF/LF churn — that is
#     what once made a shared SVG hash differently between repos).
#   • Binaries are marked `binary` so Git does not try to diff or
#     line-normalize them, but they remain normal objects.
#
# Why no LFS: these are public research / instrument repositories meant
#   to be cloned and reproduced by people and machines. LFS stores files
#   as small pointer stubs that need git-lfs installed to resolve, and it
#   carries storage/bandwidth quotas that can block downloads for everyone.
#   A text file routed through LFS becomes a broken pointer (an SVG once
#   shipped as a 129-byte stub instead of the image). Plain Git objects
#   are the most robust and the easiest to maintain and reuse.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Default: detect text and normalize line endings to LF
* text=auto eol=lf

# Text formats we author — always text, always LF, always diffable
*.md       text eol=lf
*.markdown text eol=lf
*.txt      text eol=lf
*.json     text eol=lf
*.jsonld   text eol=lf
*.csv      text eol=lf
*.tsv      text eol=lf
*.py       text eol=lf
*.r        text eol=lf
*.R        text eol=lf
*.js       text eol=lf
*.jsx      text eol=lf
*.ts       text eol=lf
*.css      text eol=lf
*.html     text eol=lf
*.xml      text eol=lf
*.yml      text eol=lf
*.yaml     text eol=lf
*.toml     text eol=lf
*.cff      text eol=lf
*.svg      text eol=lf
*.mermaid  text eol=lf
*.sh       text eol=lf

# Binary formats — kept as normal Git objects; just never diffed/normalized
*.pdf   binary
*.docx  binary
*.xlsx  binary
*.pptx  binary
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.zip   binary
*.ipynb binary
